The Whole Mf PKG 🪄💌

First & Foremost ALLLLL Glory be to God. I am so grateful to be able to bring my ideas to life and have beautiful people support me through it all. Thank you to every single one of you, it means the world to me 💌

Everything happens for a reason. I had to put a pause on my brand so I could align with genuine creatives in Arizona willing to help me with my brand in a way that’s way more hands on for me. I’d much rather be making my art myself then sending it to big factories that don’t actually hear me on what I want.

It’s a process and a journeyyy YALL. I have so many ideas for future drops and packaging I’m so excited.

Again thank you for your support❣️

I often hear people saying they aren’t flexible, so therefore they don’t think yoga is for them. The good news is yoga is so much more than just moving your body around in new ways. Pranayama which is different breathing exercises is one of the 8 limbs of yoga and personally one of my favorite. So just by consciously taking some deep breaths you are practicing yoga 🌬️🧘‍♀️
.
.
#eightlimbsofyoga #asana #pranayama #yoga

If you struggle with falling asleep, stretching may help you to do so more quickly! Can also improve blood flow and relieve muscle tension. The more you can get your body to relax before sleep, the more effective your sleep will be 💤🤍🧘‍♀️
.
.
.
#yoga #bedtimeyoga #yogaposesforbeginners

I’m sharing in the caption below something I read from yoga journal that I think is important to understand when doing heart opener poses. 💚

“Memories and experiences are stored throughout our bodies, and any kind of healing should come with the opportunity to restore and create a new experience in the body. By opening up the front body, we can identify what it’s inhabiting within us and begin reclaiming a safe space within ourselves. Sometimes we may just feel what’s in there; other times we will identify it and try to breathe through it. Fewer times, we may be able to release and connect with our bodies. But we will be there, step by step, showing up for ourselves, for our individual healing, and, by doing our personal work, we are contributing to our collective healing.

uncomfortable feelings may arise, but continue deepening your breath to remain centered in your practice. If long breaths feel unattainable, bring your attention to the part of your body that is touching the ground and do your best to stay present. If something doesn’t feel right, listen to your body to modify or simply skip the pose. The pose will always be there for you when you’re ready.”

In the videos that I have been posting recently I am typically holding those poses and taking 3-5 breaths! Wherever you are feeling the sensation breathe into that part of the body to relax more. I always say listen to your body though, it knows exactly what it needs 🫶
.
.
